stories.text:
Just received email from Google they are opening up call center for developers if they need help. Sounds promising after many years of ignoring us?

------------------------------------------------

Hello Partner, We’re always exploring ways to provide more support to developers. We launched the Google Play Developer Helpline and we’re excited to extend the invitation for you to participate. You can use the Google Play Developer Helpline in English to find more information about any Google Play policy and even resolve issues, such as policy enforcements, appeals, warnings, etc. Call us to learn how to get an app reinstated or how to appeal an enforcement. How to connect with us

    Go to the Developer Help Center.
    Open Contact Us > Let’s get started > Contact Options > Get a call.
    Complete the Helpline form.
The Helpline is available from 9 am to 6 pm local hours, Monday through Friday, excluding public holidays. We look forward to speaking with you!

stories.text: I am frustrated with doing file searches on MacOS. I used to love mdfind. It was so fast and gave me hits on everything no matter where I was in a directory. Parts of filename, or something in the file would show up on mdfind. Now it's like not giving a search. I copied the exact filename and not a hit. I tried using the regular smart folder setting it to show recent images created, modified, and opened. Fiddled around with that after changing it to 2 days I got two results. But there should be three! And even when I put down 1 day it would not show up even when it was created "Today" it should have shown up in search. The search function is totally obfuscated and I'm at loss to figure out a reliable search method for this computer. MacOS running 11.3.1
stories.title: Tips how to understand search on smart folders? or terminal's mdfind command?
